<subSubSection pageId="120" pageNumber="121" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Plant of unknown origin, cultivated in Vienna by Jacquin (not found at W).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="120" pageNumber="121" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="120" pageNumber="121">
Annual herb, commonly branched at the base with decumbent or ascending stems 5-25 cm long, vegetative parts glabrescent or shortly pubescent. Leaves 0.5-5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.3-1.5 cm, oblong-oblanceolate, apex obtuse to rounded, margin entire, basal leaves gradually narrowed into a long petiole-like base up to 2 cm in length (so appearing spathulate), stem leaves abruptly narrowed at base, sessile and sometimes clasping and auriculate. Flowers solitary, subsessile in the axils of the upper leaves, becoming crowded towards the apex; peduncles and pedicels not clearly differentiated, 0-1 mm long; bracteoles filiform, minute; sepals 2.5-3.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-3 mm, narrowly elliptic to obovate, acute to rounded, thinly pilose; corolla 1-1.1 cm long, blue with a pale tube, distinctly lobed with triangular lobes, midpetaline bands pubescent, darkish; ovary long-pilose, style divided 1-1.5 mm above base, glabrous, stigmas 2 mm. Capsule pilose with stiff coarse hairs; seeds strongly tuberculate. [
<bibRefCitation author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
: 183; 
<bibRefCitation author="Feinbrun-Dothan, N" journalOrPublisher="The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" pageId="202" pageNumber="203" pagination="33 - 43" refId="B119" refString="Feinbrun-Dothan, N, 1978. Flora Palaestina volumen 3: Ericaceae to Compositae. The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem: 33 - 43" title="Flora Palaestina volumen 3: Ericaceae to Compositae" year="1978">Feinbrun-Dothan 1978</bibRefCitation>
(plate 59); 
<bibRefCitation author="Silvestre, S" editor="Talevera, S" journalOrPublisher="Real Jardin Botanico, CSIC, Madrid" pageId="211" pageNumber="212" pagination="252 - 273" refId="B337" refString="Silvestre, S, 2012. Convolvulus. In: Talevera, S, Andres, C, Arista, M, Fernandes Piedra, MP, Gallego, MJ, Ortiz, PL, Romero Zarco, C, Salgueiro, FJ, Silvestre, S, Quinanar, A, Eds., Flora Iberica volume 11: Gentianaceae to Boraginaceae. Real Jardin Botanico, CSIC, Madrid: 252 - 273" title="Convolvulus." volumeTitle="Flora Iberica volume 11: Gentianaceae to Boraginaceae." year="2012">Silvestre 2012</bibRefCitation>
