</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="120" pageNumber="121" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="120" pageNumber="121">
Nearly circum-mediterranean but apparently absent from France, Turkey and the Balkans: Spain (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Rivas</emphasis>
s.n. [31/4/1946]); Portugal; Italy (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Todaro</emphasis>
920); Sicily (Todaro); Morocco (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Jahandiez</emphasis>
244, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Hooker</emphasis>
s.n. [5/1871]); Algeria (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Balansa</emphasis>
357, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Cosson</emphasis>
s.n. [22/5/1852]); Libya (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Pampanini &amp; Pichi-Sermolli</emphasis>
6263); Palestine (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Dinsmore</emphasis>
3721); Jordan (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Abu Laila et al</emphasis>
. 2005JOR-10-1); Syria: Jebel Druze (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Gombault</emphasis>
5961); Cyprus (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Syngrassides</emphasis>
1195).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
